The first pass confirms the main API shape: `View` is a `CustomActor` handle, copy handles point to the same object, `DownCast` returns an uninitialized handle on mismatch, and the interaction/selection traits have the signal signatures used in the draft. I’m checking the generated view surface and animation bridge now because those are the easiest places for prose to drift.
